    <text id="B0037T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell makes a request for yet another report from Jackson about his district,
                    including the ability to provide relief for the local poor.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. Tho<hi rend="super">s</hi> P. Jackson<lb/>A.S.A.
                            Com<hi rend="super">t</hi>.</name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-03-10">March 10th, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, Virginia</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>

                <p>Not having time to visit your division at present on account of recent illness,
                    please reply fully to the following questions which it is intended to have
                    incorporated in my quarterly report for April 7th.</p>

                <p>1<hi rend="super">st</hi> What is the general Condition of the Freedmen?</p>

                <p>2<hi rend="super">d</hi> What likelihood is there full and complete justice being
                    given them in cases where they are interested against Whites?</p>

                <p>3<hi rend="super">d</hi> What is the Condition of the register of Marriages as
                    authorized by <abbr expan="Circular">Cir</abbr> 11, and how far is each of the
                    four paragraphs of said Circular Carried out?</p>

                <p>4<hi rend="super">th</hi> What are the means at the disposal of the county
                    authorities for taking care of their own indigent poor? </p>

                <pb n="2"/>

                <p>5<hi rend="super">th</hi> How is the Supply of labor Adapted to the demand?</p>

                <p>6<hi rend="super">th</hi> What is the Condition of the schools already
                    established, and what the demand for them elsewhere?</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/> Your <abbr expan="Obedient Servant">Obt Serv<hi
                                rend="super">t</hi></abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/>Sub <abbr expan="Assistant">asst</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Commissioner">Com<hi rend="super">r</hi></abbr>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
